Based on the search results, here's the information about using `@modelcontextprotocol/server-brave-search` with the `BRAVE_API_KEY` environment variable via npx:

## Installation and Configuration

To set up the Brave Search MCP server, add the following configuration to your `claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "brave-search": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-brave-search"],
      "env": {
        "BRAVE_API_KEY": "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Testing the Command

You can run the server package to confirm it's accessible with: `npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/server-brave-search`

## Environment Variable Requirements

The `BRAVE_API_KEY` environment variable is required in your configuration or `.env` file. If you run the npx command without the environment variable properly set, you'll receive an error message.

## API Key Setup

To get your API key, sign up at brave.com/search/api, pick a plan (the free tier offers 2,000 queries/month), and generate your key from the dashboard.

The npx command will automatically download and run the latest version of the package, making it easy to keep the server up to date.


